FT  06 MAR 93 / Zambian coup suspects arrested
ZAMBIAN police arrested seven people yesterday, including a son of former
president Mr Kenneth Kaunda, in connection with an alleged coup plot,
Foreign Minister Vernon Mwaanga said, Reuter reports from Lusaka.
The arrests were announced after President Frederick Chiluba declared a
limited state of emergency on Thursday night. Mr Mwaanga said he had been
told by police that Major Wezi Kaunda, the former president's third son and
an opposition member of parliament under suspension for non-attendance, was
detained.
